– extent cognitive, are all persistent systems to some extent alive, or are living sys-
tems only a subset of cognitive systems? We argue that no bright line can be drawn,
and we re-assess, from this perspective, the Fermi paradox and the Drake equation.
We conclude that improving our abilities to recognize and communicate with diverse
intelligences in diverse embodiments, whether based on familiar biochemistry or not,
will either resolve or obviate the OOL problem.},
